Doesn&#x27;t that break admin-ajax.php access? It sits behind /wp-admin/. WordPress recommends allowing access when using IP whitelists.<p>Apache:<p><pre><code>  # Allow access to wp-admin/admin-ajax.php
  <Files admin-ajax.php>
      Order allow,deny
      Allow from all
      Satisfy any
  </Files>
</code></pre>
Nginx:<p><pre><code>  location /wp-admin/admin-ajax.php {
    allow all;
  }</code></pre>
